    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-xl-chicken-breast-and-sweetcorn-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-xl-chicken-breast-and-sweetcorn-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced chicken breast</strong> with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 6-7 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-xl-chicken-breast-and-sweetcorn-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under the cold tap until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then chop it roughly</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-xl-chicken-breast-and-sweetcorn-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>in a small bowl and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>stir-fry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-xl-chicken-breast-and-sweetcorn-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked through, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>sliced spring onions</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1-2 min until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-xl-chicken-breast-and-sweetcorn-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked through, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>chopped wilted spinach </strong>and <strong>drained sweetcorn </strong>to the pan</p><p>Pour in the <strong>stir-fry sauce</strong>, give it a stir<strong> </strong>and then cook for 2-3 min or until everything is warmed through and coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>Chinese-style chicken breast & sweetcorn stir-fry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-xl-chicken-breast-and-sweetcorn-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Chinese-style XL chicken breast & sweetcorn stir-fry </strong>in a bowl[s] and garnish with the <strong>remaining sliced spring onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
